    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1368<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GAL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gates</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Chief of Staff for Plans to the
                        Commander in Chief, United States Fleet</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GRAMB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gardner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">21 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_ComNavEu1">ComNavEu</gloss> passes action <gloss
                        target="#t_UnderSecNavs1">UnderSecNavs</gloss> 212100 to <gloss
                        target="#t_CominCh1">CominCh</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CNO1">CNO</gloss>
                    for <persName corresp="#p_GRAMB1">Rear Admiral Matthias B.
                    Gardner</persName>.</p>
                <p>Please see Joint Chiefs memorandum to State <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    Navy Coordinating Committee 17 July 1945<note n="1" xml:id="d1368fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1363">Document No. 1363</ref>.</note> original of which was
                    delivered to Colonel <persName corresp="#p_HGL1">Harrison Gerhardt</persName> at
                        <gloss target="#t_Terminal1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi>
                    </gloss> on 17 July 1945. It is strongly felt by Secretary<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1368fn2">i. e., Secretary of the Navy <persName corresp="#p_FJ1"
                            >James Forrestal</persName>.</note> and me that at present meeting no
                    attempt should be made to deal with Dardanelles question.…<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d1368fn3">For the last sentence of this message, see <ref
                            target="#d753">document No. 753</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
